headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 23 points, 17 rebounds and 15 assists, Jamal Murray scored 31 points, and the Denver Nuggets ended the Detroit Pistons' eight-game winning streak with a 134-119 win on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has a triple-double to help Denver snap Detroit's 8-game winning streak, 134-119

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 31 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder continued their overwhelming dominance of the Eastern Conference by beating the Atlanta Hawks 135-119 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 31 points as Thunder roll past Hawks 135-119 to continue dominance of East

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 41 points, including 12 in the fourth quarter, to help the Cleveland Cavaliers rally from 22 points down and stun the Boston Celtics 123-116 on Friday night in the final regular-season meeting of the Eastern Conference’s top...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 41, Cavaliers overcome 22-point deficit to beat the Celtics 123-116

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Shaedon Sharpe scored 25 points, Dalano Banton had 14 of his 23 points in the fourth quarter, and the Portland Trail Blazers cruised to a 121-102 victory over the Brooklyn Nets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sharpe scores 25 and Trail Blazers win 4th straight, 121-102 over Nets

headlines.description: — Davion Mitchell's 3-pointer broke a tie with 43.8 seconds left, Tyler Herro scored 29 points and the Miami Heat topped the Indiana Pacers 125-120 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell hits big 3, Herro scores 29 and Heat dig deep to top Pacers 125-120

headlines.description: — Coby White scored 24 points, including a clutch four-point play, and the Bulls rallied to beat the Toronto Raptors 125-115 in overtime on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White scores 24 points and Chicago Bulls top Raptors in overtime, 125-115

events.name: New York Knicks at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — OG Anunoby made the go-ahead 3-pointer with 5.3 seconds remaining, finishing with 19 points as the New York Knicks beat the Memphis Grizzlies 114-113 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby's 3-pointer with 5.3 seconds remaining sends Knicks past Grizzlies, 114-113

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Bol Bol scored 25 points, one shy of his career high, and the Phoenix Suns never trailed in defeating the New Orleans Pelicans 125-108 to snap a three-game skid Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bol scores 25 points and Suns snap 3-game skid with 125-108 win over shorthanded Pelicans

headlines.description: — Walker Kessler had a go-ahead dunk with 9.7 seconds left to help the Utah Jazz beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 117-116 on Friday night, snapping a six-game losing streak in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker Kessler's late dunk lifts Jazz to 117-116 win over short-handed Timberwolves

events.name: LA Clippers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 31 points on his 26th birthday and LeBron James had 28 points and 13 rebounds in the Los Angeles Lakers' fifth straight victory, 106-102 over the Los Angeles Clippers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 31 on his birthday, and the Lakers beat the Clippers 106-102 for 5 straight wins
